# Pre-push: run tests, do not push on failure

- **Before pushing:** Run the most comprehensive tests from the project root: `make test-all` (unit tests + cppcheck lint). Do not suggest or perform `git push` until tests have been run and have passed.
- **If tests fail:** Do not push. Remind to fix failures and re-run tests before pushing.
- When the user is about to push or asks to push, suggest running `make test-all` first if it hasn’t been run this session, or confirm tests passed before proceeding.
- **Timeout for `make test-all`:** The full run (unit tests + static analysis across many configs) typically takes **1–2 minutes**. When running `make test-all` via the Shell tool, use a **timeout of at least 120000 ms (2 minutes)** so the run is not cut off before completion.

**Enforcement:** To block pushes automatically when tests fail, add a git pre-push hook that runs `make test-all` and exits non-zero on failure.
